"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. I know I've talked about the absolute mind blowing properties of citronella geraniums like this one here. And the beauty of it is you can kind of uh use a soft leaf to kind of distribute some of the geranium oil on there, and you'll smell like a beautiful fragrant lemon. It's really nice. I love these things. And more than that, citronella, as we uh most of us know, is a natural anti or it's a mosquito repellent, and it works really well. But you have to stay very fragrant with it. It has to kind of you need to reapply that every 10 or 15 minutes to really get a good thing. And what I just did, I will do over all my exposed skin and go back every 10-15 minutes. I have that one in the garden. So that's my little citronella spot in the garden. But over here, this is my fence line, and I'm gonna try to put a line of citronella plants all along this fence line because these things grow just great guns around here. And over here you can see this one has really started to take off. And the idea is to grow them up into this fence, protecting it from the dogs and the chickens as it gets bigger, uh, and fill this whole area in. A lot of weeds in there, but I don't really bother with weeds. Most people know my philosophy on weeds is if you're not growing there, something should be. So you know, just let weeds happen until you're actually using that spot. Um a lot of people love black soil, I don't. The kale's doing very well. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 1.12,\n      \"end\": 2.16,\n      \"duration\": 1.04,\n      \"confidence\": 0.977,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.36,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.992\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 1.36,\n          \"end\": 1.44,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confi